@startuml tmu_service_to_remote_climate_request_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title TMU Service To Remote Climate Request Signal Flow\n(connectivity/IVI/drive context -> TMU service publish)

participant "Connectivity / IVI /\ndrive context" as ConnCtx #F4F7FB
participant "TMU\ntelematics owner" as TMU #E8F7E8
participant "TMU service bus" as TmuBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / HVAC consumers" as Obs #E8F0FE

== TMU Inputs ==

ConnCtx -> TMU : connType / signalBars\niviCpuLoad / iviMemLoad\ndriveState
TMU -> TMU : derive linkState / serviceMode from connectivity and IVI health
TMU -> TMU : remoteClimateReq = 1 only when\nserviceMode == 1 and connType == 1 and bars >= 3\nand IVI load is healthy and driveState == 0
note right of TMU
Representative gating inputs
- connType / signalBars
- iviCpuLoad / iviMemLoad
- driveState
end note

== TMU Publish ==

TMU -> TmuBus : frmTmuServiceMsg\nTmuLinkState / TmuServiceMode / RemoteClimateReq / SignalBars
note right of TMU
Representative outputs
- TmuLinkState
- TmuServiceMode
- RemoteClimateReq
- SignalBars
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

TmuBus -> Obs : remote-climate service readback /\nDATC and VCS consumers

note over ConnCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Connectivity, IVI load, and drive context reach TMU
2. TMU derives service mode and remote-climate eligibility
3. TMU publishes telematics service state and remote climate request
4. HVAC/audio consumers observe the effective telematics service posture
end note

@enduml
